==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːt|-iːt]]

===Noun===
'''pleat''' (''plural:'' '''[[pleats]]''')
# a fold in the fabric of a garment, as a part of the design of the garment, which has the purpose of adding controlled fullness or taking up excess fabric. There are many types of pleats, differing in their construction and appearance.
# A [[plait]].
===Verb===
'''pleat'''
# to form one or more pleats in a piece of fabric or a garment.
#:''A pleated skirt''

